@Fokko 

* **Readthedocs** links point to the latest GitHub version of Airflow. [link](https://airflow.readthedocs.io/en/latest/) 
* **Apache Doc** links point to latest stable release i.e. 1.9 for now. [link](https://airflow.incubator.apache.org)

@idlecool Thanks for investigating this! Given the results above, it looks like every once a while fqdn can't be resolved so it defaulted to the hostname instead. 

Not familiar with why we started with using hostname... I guess that it was easier to read and easier to implement, since for IP a host can have multiple network interfaces with multiple IPs so we'd want to make sure the right one is selected. In terms of using IP instead of fqdn,  it sounds reasonable... as long as backward compatibility is addressed.

Given that getfqdn will return hostname if it fails to resolve... I'm inclined towards your PR #2997 as a simpler solution

@clifton I'd be glad to :).

@bolkedebruin @Fokko @mistercrunch We have all travis tests passing, and I'm adding a simple "launch-kubernetes.sh" script so users can generate docker images from source and launch (the one @grantnicholas created already works for minikube, but I figure it could be a nice to have it work on full clusters as well). I also have the first draft of the operator blog ready for review. If possible, I'd love to get some feedback so I can come back with a final draft for the user-list/k8s community!

(Also, I will rebase/squash some of the more recent commits once the launch-k8s script is working)
